Solution.Description:
For managing the solution builder and underlying engine.
The following Entity level tags are utilized in this solution:
- DB: model information is generated from the spec database - IgnoreModel (RecentSolution, Template, SpecificationSource, Tag, PropertyBase): view models are not created for these entities - IgnoreView (MethodRelationship, PropertyRelationship): also, view models are not created for these, but are expected to be used in parent view models - IgnoreUI (DiagramEntity): view models, etc. created, but no specific UI created - Template (Template, SpecTemplate, CodeTemplate): for template specific rules - Specification (SpecTemplate): for spec template specific rules - ContextMenu (Solution): for custom context menus - EntityDialog (Entity, Collection, EntityReference, Method, PropertyReference, Property, Index, Relationship): have dialog controls for use in diagrams, etc. - IgnoreBuilderUI (DatabaseSource, XmlSource): for custom UI in the builder control - Source (SpecificationSource, DatabaseSource, XmlSource): for specific rules relating to sources - CustomDesigner (Diagram): for loading custom designer controls (no generated UI) - CustomEvents (Diagram, DIagramEntity): for items with custom events that require custom disposal, etc. - CustomUpdate (Diagram, DIagramEntity): for items with custom events that require custom update, custom is edited, etc. - CustomPaste (Entity, Parameter, RelationshipProperty): for items requiring a custom paste method - CustomMouseMove (Property): for handling custom version of this method - CustomCollectionContext (XmlNode, XmlAttribute): for handling custom version of this method
